You must be able to explain some specifics about this infrastructure:

What is a server
 - A server is a device (physical or virtual) that listens to requests of other 
   devices (clients) to return some kind of response or functionality

What is the role of the domain name
 - The domain name is there to provide a human-readable address to users so they don't have to memorize an IP.

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
 - A CNAME record that points to another domain name.

What is the role of the web server
 - Listen to HTTP and HTTPS requests, and redirect accordingly to other internal servers.
 - It is usually used to return static content like pre-rendered HTML from the backend.

What is the role of the application server
 - It is the main business logic of the application and does all the information processing.

What is the role of the database
 - Store persisting data that remains through server restarts and sessions.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
 - The client's request travels through the TCP/IP protocol, where it first the URL "www.foobar.com" is translated by
   a DNS server to get the actual IP address of the servers.
 - The request most likely will be using the HTTP or HTTPS protocol.


You must be able to explain what the issues are with this infrastructure:

SPOF
 - Since all our infrastructure sits inside one server, if this server ever goes down clients won't be able to access it.

Downtime when maintenance needed (like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted)
 - The application can't be accessed during maintenance because there is no redundancy.
 - This may have less effect on scheduled maintenance but will be very problematic in unexpected failures.

Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic
 - There is no room to scale other than adding virtual application servers and use the NGINX web server as a load-balancer.
 - This may hinder the server's performance.
